<object program="/usr/SkotOS/sys/tip">
  <Tips:Tip>
    <Tips:Topic topic="intro">
      <Tips:Description desc="TIP: To get around in the game, type commands (imperatives). It's like giving instructions to a robot. To leave your room, type \"go east\" (without the quotes). \"east\" will work too. Type \"tip\" to learn how to get more help."/>
      <Tips:Description desc="TIP: The \"tip\" command can be typed repeatedly to read through an initial set of information. Each time you type it, you will learn a little bit more about how to issue commands and where to go in Castle Marrach. Type \"tip\" (without the quotes) again for information on other help resources."/>
      <Tips:Description desc="TIP: Help files offer instructions on a number of basic commands. Type \"help concepts\" to get a list of help files available. Type \"tip\" again to learn how to get in-game assistance."/>
      <Tips:Description desc="TIP: Online StoryHosts are available 3pm to 6pm Pacific Time, Monday-Friday. StoryGuides and StoryPlotters are here all hours on a volunteer basis. Type \"assist\" if you need their help. For example: assist \"I can not find the tailor.\" Type \"tip\" again to learn how to communicate with other players.'"/>
      <Tips:Description desc="TIP: Other players may offer you help. These are probably kind souls who want to be of assistance, so be nice to them. You can respond by using the say verb. For example: \"say 'Hello.'\". Type \"help communicate\" for more in-depth information on talking. Type \"tip\" again for information on how to access full maps."/>
      <Tips:Description desc="TIP: You started out in your guest room and should now have moved out into the corridor. You're currently on the second floor of the castle. Click on the map at the right and a complete map of the outer bailey will appear. You're in the long corridor to the west of the Alchemist's hall. Type \"tip\" again to learn about perception."/>
      <Tips:Description desc="TIP: To look at your surroundings, type \"look\". To look at something specific, type \"look at [name]\". Type \"help perception\" for more information on these commands. Type \"tip\" again to learn how to examine things more in-depth."/>
      <Tips:Description desc="TIP: To look at something in greater detail, type \"examine [item]\" or \"examine\" alone to view a room. Examine takes a few moments; there will be a delay. Type \"tip\" again to learn about fashion."/>
      <Tips:Description desc="TIP: Type \"look at me\" or \"examine me\" to see what you're wearing right now. You'll want to find some clothes to replace those unstylish wraps. Type \"tip\" again to learn where to replace your wraps."/>
      <Tips:Description desc="TIP: Men's clothes are available from the tailor on the third floor; women's clothes are available from the seamstress, also on the third floor. Type \"tip\" again to learn how to move around."/>
      <Tips:Description desc="TIP: To move, type a command such as \"go north\". You can abbreviate this as \"north\" or \"n\". You can also use the enter command to go through entrances: \"enter archway\". Type \"help movement\" for more information on moving. Type \"tip\" again to discover how to find the exits in your current room."/>
      <Tips:Description desc="TIP: Type \"exits\" to see exits in your current room. Type \"tip\" again for directions to the seamstress and tailor."/>
      <Tips:Description desc="TIP: TIP: Walk north till you go to the grandfather clock, then go: e, e, s, e, n, up, s, w, w, n, w, w, w, s. The tailor will be northwest and the seamstress southwest. Type \"tip\" again to learn how to talk to the seamstress and tailor."/>
      <Tips:Description desc="TIP: The Seamstress and Tailor are CNPCs (Computer NPCs). Type \"ask tailor\" or \"ask seamstress\" to get a listing of available clothing. Type \"ask seamstress for [clothing item]\" or \"ask tailor for [clothing item]\" to receive it. Type \"tip\" again to learn where other players hang out."/>
      <Tips:Description desc="TIP: Once you're clothed, you'll want to find the other players. Top hangouts are the Dining Hall and the Dining Hall East. Type \"tip\" again for directions to these locales."/>
      <Tips:Description desc="TIP: The Dining Halls are on the ground floor. Return to the stairs and descend to the ground floor. Leaving the stairway, you'll enter into a large courtyard. Go \"west\" down the grand passage. The Dining Hall is just north. The Dining Hall East is east of the Dining Hall. Type \"tip\" again for more information on talking to people."/>
      <Tips:Description desc="TIP: You can use many verbs other than \"say\" to talk to people. Words can describe how you are responding, such as \"ask\", \"reply\", \"remark\", \"comment\", and \"state\". For example, type \"announce 'Greetings Friends.'\" Type \"tip\" again to learn about gestures."/>
      <Tips:Description desc="TIP: You can also communicate with facial expressions and gestures such as \"smile\", \"grin\", \"frown\", \"smirk\", \"wave\", \"clap\", etc. Type \"tip\" again for information on adverbs."/>
      <Tips:Description desc="TIP: Most commands allow adverbs such as \"smile softly\", \"frown grimly\", or \"ask politely, 'Can you help me?'\". Type \"tip\" again to learn how to view lists of adverbs."/>
      <Tips:Description desc="TIP: You can get lists of adverbs by typing incomplete adverbs. For example, if you wanted to smile and wanted to see what adverbs started with a, you could type \"smile a\". \"smile ad\" or \"smile av\" will produce a shorter list. Type \"tip\" again to learn how to abbreviate adverbs."/>
      <Tips:Description desc="TIP: You can also abbreviate adverbs. If there is only one match, it will be the one used. \"ask sof\" is the same as \"ask softly\" (ie, \"ask sof 'are you OK?'\") Tip \"tip\" again to learn about moving around inside a room."/>
      <Tips:Description desc="TIP: When you enter a new area you begin near the entrance from where you arrived. You can \"approach [item]\" to move near a different place. For example, \"approach wooden table\". Type \"help prox\" for more information on proximities. Type \"tip\" again to learn about approaching people."/>
      <Tips:Description desc="TIP: You may also \"approach\" a person to be near them. However, the person must give their consent before you may enter their personal space. Type \"help consent\" to learn about the consent system. Type \"tip\" again to learn more about interacting with the contents of the room."/>
      <Tips:Description desc="TIP: You can interact with the contents of a room by entering into stances. For example, you can \"kneel before long wooden table\" or \"sit at long wooden table\" or \"stand near long wooden table\". Type \"help stance\" for more information. Type \"tip\" again to learn about the interrelation of stances and people."/>
      <Tips:Description desc="TIP: \"sit by [person]\", \"kneel before [person]\" or other similar commands that put you in close proximity to someone also require consent. Type \"tip\" again to get information on giving consent."/>
      <Tips:Description desc="TIP: If someone tries to enter your personal space, you will get a message announcing the action. You can type \"allow [name]\" to allow their action or \"deny [name]\" to deny their action. Type \"tip\" again to learn how to leave proximities."/>
      <Tips:Description desc="TIP: To leave the proximity of an object or person, type \"leave\". Or, enter a new proximity: \"sit near pillars\". Type \"tip\" again for a reminder on how to get help in Castle Marrach."/>
      <Tips:Description desc="TIP: Type \"help\" for a list of the help topics. Type \"assist '[message]' at any hour. If a StoryGuide is available, you will receive a response soon after. If not, they will look for you later. Type \"tip\" again for information on other Castle Marrach resources."/>
      <Tips:Description desc="TIP: The Marrach Web Pages has more great information. Visit www.skotos.net/games/marrach. The tutorial has more detailed information on how to input commands. The background files to the bottom give more information on the Castle itself. The events area always talks about upcoming happenings. The forums area always lists the most relevent discussions on our bulletin boards. Type \"tip\" again to learn about bug reporting."/>
      <Tips:Description desc="TIP: You can log bugs by typing \"bug [bug description]\", ideas with \"idea [idea comment]\", and typos with \"typo [typo description]\". Type \"help bugs\" for more information on these topics. Type \"tip\" again to receive the final tip."/>
      <Tips:Description desc="TIP: This is the final tip. Type \"tip\" again to view the tips again."/>
    </Tips:Topic>
    <Tips:Topic topic="sword">
      <Tips:Description desc="Swords are very pointy."/>
      <Tips:Description desc="Swords are sharp."/>
      <Tips:Description desc="Swords are dangerous. Handle with care."/>
      <Tips:Description desc="Use the pointy end."/>
      <Tips:Description desc="Swords are very very sharp."/>
      <Tips:Description desc="Swords are very pointy."/>
    </Tips:Topic>
  </Tips:Tip>
</object>
